+## Overview
+
+Between May 2 and May 21, 2026, the company recorded 30 orders with total revenue of $7,154.44. The median order value was $204.94. Sales spanned four products (Widget, Gadget, Sprocket, Doohickey) and four regions (North, South, East, West).
+
+## Top Products
+
+Gadget led all products with $2,392.00 in revenue from just 16 units, thanks to its $149.50 price point. Widget followed at $2,118.94 on 106 units, appearing in more orders than any other product. Doohickey earned $1,513.00 from 17 units, while Sprocket ranked last with $1,130.50 despite moving 238 units — by far the highest volume — at only $4.75 each.
+
+## Regional Performance
+
+North was the strongest region at $2,176.35, driven by steady Widget volume and two Gadget orders. East followed with $1,830.79 and South with $1,732.48. West trailed at $1,414.82, the only region below $1,500, with lower unit counts across most of its orders.
+
+## Recommendations
+
+- Gadget generated $2,392.00 from only 16 units; prioritize Gadget marketing, since each additional sale adds $149.50 in revenue.
+- Sprocket sold 238 units yet earned just $1,130.50; consider raising its $4.75 price or bundling it with higher-margin products.
+- West trails all regions at $1,414.82, roughly 35% below North's $2,176.35; target West with focused sales attention.
